A national polytechnic tutor was on Monday arraigned before Winam Law court and charged with threatening to kill and creating disturbances. The accused, Philimon Bulwa, 42,  appeared before senior resident magistrate C. N Oruwo and pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Oruwo released the accused on a bond of Sh80, 000 or cash bail of Sh 25,000. Bulwa, an ex-prison officer, is a tutor at the Kisumu National polytechnic. He allegedly threatened to kill the institution's chief principal Catherine Kelonye. He was arrested after Kelonye reported the case on July 7, 2022.  Kisumu Central sub-county police commander Anthony Maina confirmed the arrest of the suspect. Maina said the suspect was arrested by officers from Kondele Police Station. Bulwa, was taken to court following the recommendation from the Office of the Director of Public Prosecution (ODPP), Nyanza region. “The case was investigated and the file forwarded to ODPP for perusal and advice,” Maina said.